body_html: @aselle No, it is not resolved. Working with the mobilenet quantization, still need to add the argument --copt="-DTENSORFLOW_DISABLE_META" when building the "libtensorflow_inference.so" file. But this made the performance slower. When using the nightly-android builds, the result is different between mobile and PC.

body: @aselle No, it is not resolved. Working with the mobilenet quantization, still need to add the argument --copt="-DTENSORFLOW_DISABLE_META" when building the "libtensorflow_inference.so" file. But this made the performance slower. When using the nightly-android builds, the result is different between mobile and PC.
